This is for a specific student starting english tutoring in term 3 week 9.


Year 10 English Tutoring Plan - NSW Syllabus Aligned
Stage 5 (Years 9-10) Specific Outcomes & Content
CURRENT SYLLABUS OUTCOMES TO TARGET:
Reading, viewing and listening to texts:

EN5-RVL-01: Uses a range of personal, creative and critical strategies to engage with increasingly challenging texts
EN5-RVL-02: Analyses representations of social, cultural and personal identity in texts

Understanding and responding to texts:

EN5-URA-01: Analyses how meaning is created through the use and interpretation of increasingly complex language forms, features and structures
EN5-URB-01: Analyses how authors create meaning by including distinctive ideas, themes and texts' intended purposes

Expressing ideas and composing texts:

EN5-ECA-01: Crafts sustained written, spoken, visual, digital and multimodal texts to experiment with and evaluate alternative interpretations
EN5-ECB-01: Plans, edits and publishes texts for various audiences and purposes using appropriate form, content, style and language choices


TERM 3 WEEKS 9-10 (IMMEDIATE FOCUS)
Week 9: Assessment Support & Text Analysis
Target Outcomes: EN5-URA-01, EN5-URB-01

Syllabus Focus: Language forms, features and structures
Content Points to Cover:

How authors use language techniques to create meaning
Identifying themes and author's purpose in current class text
Analysis of characterisation and setting


Assessment Support: Help with current assignments using analytical framework

Week 10: Term Consolidation
Target Outcomes: EN5-RVL-01, EN5-ECA-01

Syllabus Focus: Personal and critical engagement strategies
Content Points to Cover:

Review different strategies for engaging with texts
Consolidate understanding of text analysis techniques
Prepare for Term 4 requirements




TERM 4 DETAILED BREAKDOWN
Weeks 1-2: New Text Introduction & Context
Target Outcomes: EN5-RVL-01, EN5-RVL-02
Syllabus Content:

Text selection strategies for different purposes
Understanding social, cultural and historical contexts
Identifying representations of identity in texts

Specific Learning Points:

How to research and understand context of prescribed text
Identifying different types of identity representation
Personal engagement strategies with unfamiliar texts

Weeks 3-4: Language Analysis & Meaning
Target Outcomes: EN5-URA-01, EN5-URB-01
Syllabus Content:

Complex language forms: syntax, imagery, symbolism
Distinctive ideas and themes analysis
Author's craft and intended purpose

Specific Learning Points:

Systematic identification of language techniques
Analysis of how techniques create specific effects
Understanding theme vs. topic distinction
Linking author's choices to intended audience/purpose

Weeks 5-6: Composition & Alternative Interpretations
Target Outcomes: EN5-ECA-01, EN5-ECB-01
Syllabus Content:

Sustained analytical writing
Experimental interpretation approaches
Planning and drafting for different audiences

Specific Learning Points:

Essay planning using syllabus requirements
Developing alternative interpretations of same text
Audience awareness in writing
Integration of evidence and analysis

Weeks 7-8: Critical Analysis & Evaluation
Target Outcomes: EN5-URA-01, EN5-URB-01, EN5-ECA-01
Syllabus Content:

Evaluation of textual interpretations
Critical reading strategies
Sophisticated analysis of meaning-making

Specific Learning Points:

Comparing multiple interpretations of texts
Evaluating strength of different analytical approaches
Using critical reading to support own interpretations
Moving beyond surface-level analysis

Weeks 9-10: Assessment Preparation & Publication
Target Outcomes: EN5-ECB-01, EN5-ECA-01
Syllabus Content:

Publishing for specific audiences and purposes
Editing and refining sustained texts
Final evaluation of learning

Specific Learning Points:

Meeting assessment criteria systematically
Editing for clarity and sophisticated expression
Self-evaluation against syllabus outcomes
Portfolio completion and reflection